169  static FILE *_internalFileOpener(const char *fn, const char *mode)
170  {
171  FILE *fp = nullptr;
172 
173  #ifndef WIN32
174  fp = fopen(fn, mode);
175  #else
176  if(fopen_s(&fp, fn, mode) != 0)
177  {
178  fp = nullptr;
179  }
180  #endif
181 
182  return fp;
183  }
184 
185  #define JSON_SERIALIZED_CLASS(_cn) \
186  class _cn; \
187  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const _cn& p); \
188  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, _cn& p);
189 
190  #define IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(_cn) \
191  public: \
192  static void document(const char *path = nullptr) \
193  { \
194  _cn example; \
195  example.initForDocumenting(); \
196  std::string theJson = example.serialize(3); \
197  std::cout << "------------------------------------------------" << std::endl \
198  << #_cn << std::endl \
199  << theJson << std::endl \
200  << "------------------------------------------------" << std::endl; \
201  \
202  if(path != nullptr && path[0] != 0) \
203  { \
204  std::string fn = path; \
205  fn.append("/"); \
206  fn.append(#_cn); \
207  fn.append(".json"); \
208  \
209  FILE *fp = _internalFileOpener(fn.c_str(), "wt");\
210  \
211  if(fp != nullptr) \
212  { \
213  fputs(theJson.c_str(), fp); \
214  fclose(fp); \
215  } \
216  else \
217  { \
218  std::cout << "ERROR: Cannot write to " << fn << std::endl; \
219  } \
220  } \
221  } \
222  static const char *className() \
223  { \
224  return #_cn; \
225  }
226 
227  #define IMPLEMENT_JSON_SERIALIZATION() \
228  public: \
229  bool deserialize(const char *s) \
230  { \
231  try \
232  { \
233  if(s != nullptr && s[0] != 0) \
234  { \
235  from_json(nlohmann::json::parse(s), *this); \
236  } \
237  else \
238  { \
239  return false; \
240  } \
241  } \
242  catch(...) \
243  { \
244  return false; \
245  } \
246  return true; \
247  } \
248  \
249  std::string serialize(const int indent = -1) \
250  { \
251  nlohmann::json j; \
252  to_json(j, *this); \
253  return j.dump(indent); \
254  }
255 
256  #define IMPLEMENT_WRAPPED_JSON_SERIALIZATION(_cn) \
257  public: \
258  std::string serializeWrapped(const int indent = -1) \
259  { \
260  nlohmann::json j; \
261  to_json(j, *this); \
262  \
263  std::string rc; \
264  char firstChar[2]; \
265  firstChar[0] = #_cn[0]; \
266  firstChar[1] = 0; \
267  firstChar[0] = tolower(firstChar[0]); \
268  rc.assign("{\""); \
269  rc.append(firstChar); \
270  rc.append((#_cn) + 1); \
271  rc.append("\":"); \
272  rc.append(j.dump(indent)); \
273  rc.append("}"); \
274  \
275  return rc; \
276  }
277 
278  #define TOJSON_IMPL(__var) \
279  {#__var, p.__var}
280 
281  #define FROMJSON_IMPL_SIMPLE(__var) \
282  getOptional(#__var, p.__var, j)
283 
284  #define FROMJSON_IMPL(__var, __type, __default) \
285  getOptional<__type>(#__var, p.__var, j, __default)

289  static std::string EMPTY_STRING;
290 
291  template<class T>
292  static void getOptional(const char *name, T& v, const nlohmann::json& j, T def)
293  {
294  try
295  {
296  if(j.contains(name))
297  {
298  j.at(name).get_to(v);
299  }
300  else
301  {
302  v = def;
303  }
304  }
305  catch(...)
306  {
307  v = def;
308  }
309  }
310 
311  template<class T>
312  static void getOptional(const char *name, T& v, const nlohmann::json& j)
313  {
314  try
315  {
316  if(j.contains(name))
317  {
318  j.at(name).get_to(v);
319  }
320  }
321  catch(...)
322  {
323  }
324  }
325 
326  template<class T>
327  static void getOptionalWithIndicator(const char *name, T& v, const nlohmann::json& j, T def, bool *wasFound)
328  {
329  try
330  {
331  if(j.contains(name))
332  {
333  j.at(name).get_to(v);
334  *wasFound = true;
335  }
336  else
337  {
338  v = def;
339  *wasFound = false;
340  }
341  }
342  catch(...)
343  {
344  v = def;
345  *wasFound = false;
346  }
347  }
348 
349  template<class T>
350  static void getOptionalWithIndicator(const char *name, T& v, const nlohmann::json& j, bool *wasFound)
351  {
352  try
353  {
354  if(j.contains(name))
355  {
356  j.at(name).get_to(v);
357  *wasFound = true;
358  }
359  else
360  {
361  *wasFound = false;
362  }
363  }
364  catch(...)
365  {
366  *wasFound = false;
367  }
368  }

370  class ConfigurationObjectBase
371  {
372  public:
373  ConfigurationObjectBase()
374  {
375  _documenting = false;
376  }
377 
378  virtual ~ConfigurationObjectBase()
379  {
380  }
381 
382  virtual void initForDocumenting()
383  {
384  _documenting = true;
385  }
386 
387  virtual std::string toString()
388  {
389  return std::string("");
390  }
391 
392  inline virtual bool isDocumenting() const
393  {
394  return _documenting;
395  }
396 
397  protected:
398  bool _documenting;
399  };

404  JSON_SERIALIZED_CLASS(WatchdogSettings)
405  class WatchdogSettings : public ConfigurationObjectBase
406  {
407  IMPLEMENT_JSON_SERIALIZATION()
408  IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(WatchdogSettings)
409 
410  public:
412  bool enabled;
413 
415  int intervalMs;
416 
418  int hangDetectionMs;
419 
421  bool abortOnHang;
422 
424  int slowExecutionThresholdMs;
425 
426  WatchdogSettings()
427  {
428  clear();
429  }
430 
431  void clear()
432  {
433  enabled = true;
434  intervalMs = 5000;
435  hangDetectionMs = 2000;
436  abortOnHang = true;
437  slowExecutionThresholdMs = 100;
438  }
439 
440  virtual void initForDocumenting()
441  {
442  clear();
443  }
444  };
445 
446  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const WatchdogSettings& p)
447  {
448  j = nlohmann::json{
449  TOJSON_IMPL(enabled),
450  TOJSON_IMPL(intervalMs),
451  TOJSON_IMPL(hangDetectionMs),
452  TOJSON_IMPL(abortOnHang),
453  TOJSON_IMPL(slowExecutionThresholdMs)
454  };
455  }
456  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, WatchdogSettings& p)
457  {
458  p.clear();
459  getOptional<bool>("enabled", p.enabled, j, true);
460  getOptional<int>("intervalMs", p.intervalMs, j, 5000);
461  getOptional<int>("hangDetectionMs", p.hangDetectionMs, j, 2000);
462  getOptional<bool>("abortOnHang", p.abortOnHang, j, true);
463  getOptional<int>("slowExecutionThresholdMs", p.slowExecutionThresholdMs, j, 100);
464  }

523 
524  public:
525  std::string id;
526  std::string name;
527  std::string description;
528  std::string comments;
529  int count;
530  int used; // NOTE: Ignored during deserialization!
531 
532  Feature()
533  {
534  clear();
535  }
536 
537  void clear()
538  {
539  id.clear();
540  name.clear();
541  description.clear();
542  comments.clear();
543  count = 0;
544  used = 0;
545  }
546 
547  virtual void initForDocumenting()
548  {
549  clear();
550  id = "{af9540d1-3e86-4fa6-8b80-e26daecb61ab}";
551  name = "A sample feature";
552  description = "This is an example of a feature";
553  comments = "These are comments for this feature";
554  count = 42;
555  used = 16;
556  }
557  };
558 
559  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const Feature& p)
560  {
561  j = nlohmann::json{
562  TOJSON_IMPL(id),
563  TOJSON_IMPL(name),
564  TOJSON_IMPL(description),
565  TOJSON_IMPL(comments),
566  TOJSON_IMPL(count),
567  TOJSON_IMPL(used)
568  };
569  }
570  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, Feature& p)
571  {
572  p.clear();
573  j.at("id").get_to(p.id);
574  getOptional("name", p.name, j);
575  getOptional("description", p.description, j);
576  getOptional("comments", p.comments, j);
577  getOptional("count", p.count, j, 0);
578 
579  // NOTE: Not deserialized!
580  //getOptional("used", p.used, j, 0);
581  }

719  IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(RtpPayloadTypeTranslation)
720 
721  public:
723  uint16_t external;
724 
726  uint16_t engage;
727 
728  RtpPayloadTypeTranslation()
729  {
730  clear();
731  }
732 
733  void clear()
734  {
735  external = 0;
736  engage = 0;
737  }
738 
739  bool matches(const RtpPayloadTypeTranslation& other)
740  {
741  return ( (external == other.external) && (engage == other.engage) );
742  }
743  };
744

746  {

753  {
754  p.clear();
755  getOptional<uint16_t>("external", p.external, j);
756  getOptional<uint16_t>("engage", p.engage, j);
757  }

953  JSON_SERIALIZED_CLASS(BlobInfo)

1281  JSON_SERIALIZED_CLASS(Location)
1293  class Location : public ConfigurationObjectBase
1294  {
1295  IMPLEMENT_JSON_SERIALIZATION()
1296  IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(Location)
1297 
1298  public:
1299  constexpr static double INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE = -999.999;
1300 
1302  uint32_t ts;
1303 
1305  double latitude;
1306 
1308  double longitude;
1309 
1311  double altitude;
1312 
1314  double direction;
1315 
1317  double speed;
1318 
1319  Location()
1320  {
1321  clear();
1322  }
1323 
1324  void clear()
1325  {
1326  ts = 0;
1327  latitude = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1328  longitude = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1329  altitude = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1330  direction = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1331  speed = INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE;
1332  }
1333 
1334  virtual void initForDocumenting()
1335  {
1336  clear();
1337 
1338  ts = 123456;
1339  latitude = 123.456;
1340  longitude = 456.789;
1341  altitude = 123;
1342  direction = 1;
1343  speed = 1234;
1344  }
1345  };
1346 
1347  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const Location& p)
1348  {
1349  if(p.latitude != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE && p.longitude != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE)
1350  {
1351  j = nlohmann::json{
1352  TOJSON_IMPL(latitude),
1353  TOJSON_IMPL(longitude),
1354  };
1355 
1356  if(p.ts != 0) j["ts"] = p.ts;
1357  if(p.altitude != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE) j["altitude"] = p.altitude;
1358  if(p.speed != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE) j["speed"] = p.speed;
1359  if(p.direction != Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE) j["direction"] = p.direction;
1360  }
1361  }
1362  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, Location& p)
1363  {
1364  p.clear();
1365  getOptional<uint32_t>("ts", p.ts, j, 0);
1366  j.at("latitude").get_to(p.latitude);
1367  j.at("longitude").get_to(p.longitude);
1368  getOptional<double>("altitude", p.altitude, j, Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE);
1369  getOptional<double>("direction", p.direction, j, Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE);
1370  getOptional<double>("speed", p.speed, j, Location::INVALID_LOCATION_VALUE);
1371  }

2007  typedef enum
2008  {
2010  rtUndefined = 0,
2011 
2013  rtWhitelist = 1,
2014 
2016  rtBlacklist = 2
2017  } RestrictionType_t;
2018 
2019  static bool isValidRestrictionType(RestrictionType_t t)
2020  {
2021  return (t == RestrictionType_t::rtUndefined ||
2022  t == RestrictionType_t::rtWhitelist ||
2023  t == RestrictionType_t::rtBlacklist );
2024  }

2128  JSON_SERIALIZED_CLASS(Rallypoint)
2136  class Rallypoint : public ConfigurationObjectBase
2137  {
2138  IMPLEMENT_JSON_SERIALIZATION()
2139  IMPLEMENT_JSON_DOCUMENTATION(Rallypoint)
2140 
2141  public:
2142 
2147  NetworkAddress host;
2148 
2160  std::string certificate;
2161 
2173  std::string certificateKey;
2174 
2178  bool verifyPeer;
2179 
2183  bool allowSelfSignedCertificate;
2184 
2188  std::vector<std::string> caCertificates;
2189 
2193  int transactionTimeoutMs;
2194 
2198  bool disableMessageSigning;
2199 
2201  int connectionTimeoutSecs;
2202 
2204  TcpNetworkTxOptions tcpTxOptions;
2205 
2206  Rallypoint()
2207  {
2208  clear();
2209  }
2210 
2211  void clear()
2212  {
2213  host.clear();
2214  certificate.clear();
2215  certificateKey.clear();
2216  caCertificates.clear();
2217  verifyPeer = false;
2218  transactionTimeoutMs = 5000;
2219  disableMessageSigning = false;
2220  connectionTimeoutSecs = 5;
2221  tcpTxOptions.clear();
2222  }
2223 
2224  bool matches(const Rallypoint& other)
2225  {
2226  if(!host.matches(other.host))
2227  {
2228  return false;
2229  }
2230 
2231  if(certificate.compare(other.certificate) != 0)
2232  {
2233  return false;
2234  }
2235 
2236  if(certificateKey.compare(other.certificateKey) != 0)
2237  {
2238  return false;
2239  }
2240 
2241  if(verifyPeer != other.verifyPeer)
2242  {
2243  return false;
2244  }
2245 
2246  if(allowSelfSignedCertificate != other.allowSelfSignedCertificate)
2247  {
2248  return false;
2249  }
2250 
2251  if(caCertificates.size() != other.caCertificates.size())
2252  {
2253  return false;
2254  }
2255 
2256  for(size_t x = 0; x < caCertificates.size(); x++)
2257  {
2258  bool found = false;
2259 
2260  for(size_t y = 0; y < other.caCertificates.size(); y++)
2261  {
2262  if(caCertificates[x].compare(other.caCertificates[y]) == 0)
2263  {
2264  found = true;
2265  break;
2266  }
2267  }
2268 
2269  if(!found)
2270  {
2271  return false;
2272  }
2273  }
2274 
2275  if(transactionTimeoutMs != other.transactionTimeoutMs)
2276  {
2277  return false;
2278  }
2279 
2280  if(disableMessageSigning != other.disableMessageSigning)
2281  {
2282  return false;
2283  }
2284 
2285  return true;
2286  }
2287  };
2288 
2289  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const Rallypoint& p)
2290  {
2291  j = nlohmann::json{
2292  TOJSON_IMPL(host),
2293  TOJSON_IMPL(certificate),
2294  TOJSON_IMPL(certificateKey),
2295  TOJSON_IMPL(verifyPeer),
2296  TOJSON_IMPL(allowSelfSignedCertificate),
2297  TOJSON_IMPL(caCertificates),
2298  TOJSON_IMPL(transactionTimeoutMs),
2299  TOJSON_IMPL(disableMessageSigning),
2300  TOJSON_IMPL(connectionTimeoutSecs),
2301  TOJSON_IMPL(tcpTxOptions)
2302  };
2303  }
2304 
2305  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, Rallypoint& p)
2306  {
2307  p.clear();
2308  j.at("host").get_to(p.host);
2309  getOptional("certificate", p.certificate, j);
2310  getOptional("certificateKey", p.certificateKey, j);
2311  getOptional<bool>("verifyPeer", p.verifyPeer, j, true);
2312  getOptional<bool>("allowSelfSignedCertificate", p.allowSelfSignedCertificate, j, false);
2313  getOptional<std::vector<std::string>>("caCertificates", p.caCertificates, j);
2314  getOptional<int>("transactionTimeoutMs", p.transactionTimeoutMs, j, 5000);
2315  getOptional<bool>("disableMessageSigning", p.disableMessageSigning, j, false);
2316  getOptional<int>("connectionTimeoutSecs", p.connectionTimeoutSecs, j, 5);
2317  getOptional<TcpNetworkTxOptions>("tcpTxOptions", p.tcpTxOptions, j);
2318  }

4275  TOJSON_IMPL(rxImpairment),
4276

4279 
4280  // TODO: need a better way to indicate whether rtpProfile is present
4281  if(p._wasDeserialized_rtpProfile || p.isDocumenting())
4282  {
4283  j["rtpProfile"] = p.rtpProfile;
4284  }
4285 
4286  if(p.isDocumenting())
4287  {
4288  j["rallypointCluster"] = p.rallypointCluster;
4289  j["rallypoints"] = p.rallypoints;
4290  }
4291  else
4292  {
4293  // rallypointCluster takes precedence if it has elements
4294  if(!p.rallypointCluster.rallypoints.empty())
4295  {
4296  j["rallypointCluster"] = p.rallypointCluster;
4297  }
4298  else if(!p.rallypoints.empty())
4299  {
4300  j["rallypoints"] = p.rallypoints;
4301  }
4302  }

4304  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, Group& p)
4305  {
4306  p.clear();
4307  j.at("type").get_to(p.type);
4308  getOptional<Group::BridgingOpMode_t>("bom", p.bom, j, Group::BridgingOpMode_t::bomRaw);
4309  j.at("id").get_to(p.id);
4310  getOptional<std::string>("name", p.name, j);
4311  getOptional<std::string>("interfaceName", p.interfaceName, j);
4312  getOptional<NetworkAddress>("rx", p.rx, j);
4313  getOptional<NetworkAddress>("tx", p.tx, j);
4314  getOptional<NetworkTxOptions>("txOptions", p.txOptions, j);
4315  getOptional<std::string>("cryptoPassword", p.cryptoPassword, j);
4316  getOptional<std::string>("alias", p.alias, j);
4317  getOptional<TxAudio>("txAudio", p.txAudio, j);
4318  getOptional<Presence>("presence", p.presence, j);
4319  getOptional<std::vector<Rallypoint>>("rallypoints", p.rallypoints, j);
4320  getOptional<RallypointCluster>("rallypointCluster", p.rallypointCluster, j);
4321  getOptional<Audio>("audio", p.audio, j);
4322  getOptional<GroupTimeline>("timeline", p.timeline, j);
4323  getOptional<bool>("blockAdvertising", p.blockAdvertising, j, false);
4324  getOptional<std::string>("source", p.source, j);
4325  getOptional<int>("maxRxSecs", p.maxRxSecs, j, 0);
4326  getOptional<bool>("enableMulticastFailover", p.enableMulticastFailover, j, false);
4327  getOptional<int>("multicastFailoverSecs", p.multicastFailoverSecs, j, 10);
4328  getOptional<NetworkAddress>("rtcpPresenceRx", p.rtcpPresenceRx, j);
4329  getOptional<bool>("enableRxVad", p.enableRxVad, j, false);
4330  getOptional<std::vector<std::string>>("presenceGroupAffinities", p.presenceGroupAffinities, j);

9055 
9057  omPayloadTransformation = 1,
9058 
9060  omAnonymousMixing = 2

9382  {
9383  id.clear();
9384  serviceConfigurationFileCheckSecs = 60;
9385  groupsConfigurationFileName.clear();
9386  groupsConfigurationFileCommand.clear();
9387  groupsConfigurationFileCheckSecs = 60;
9388  statusReport.clear();
9389  externalHealthCheckResponder.clear();
9390  internals.clear();
9391  certStoreFileName.clear();
9392  certStorePasswordHex.clear();
9393  enginePolicy.clear();
9394  configurationCheckSignalName = "rts.9a164fa.${id}";
9395  }
9396  };
9397 
9398  static void to_json(nlohmann::json& j, const EarServerConfiguration& p)
9399  {
9400  j = nlohmann::json{
9401  TOJSON_IMPL(id),
9402  TOJSON_IMPL(serviceConfigurationFileCheckSecs),
9403  TOJSON_IMPL(groupsConfigurationFileName),
9404  TOJSON_IMPL(groupsConfigurationFileCommand),
9405  TOJSON_IMPL(groupsConfigurationFileCheckSecs),
9406  TOJSON_IMPL(statusReport),
9407  TOJSON_IMPL(externalHealthCheckResponder),
9408  TOJSON_IMPL(internals),
9409  TOJSON_IMPL(certStoreFileName),
9410  TOJSON_IMPL(certStorePasswordHex),
9411  TOJSON_IMPL(enginePolicy),
9412  TOJSON_IMPL(configurationCheckSignalName)
9413  };
9414  }
9415  static void from_json(const nlohmann::json& j, EarServerConfiguration& p)
9416  {
9417  p.clear();
9418  getOptional<std::string>("id", p.id, j);
9419  getOptional<int>("serviceConfigurationFileCheckSecs", p.serviceConfigurationFileCheckSecs, j, 60);
9420  getOptional<std::string>("groupsConfigurationFileName", p.groupsConfigurationFileName, j);
9421  getOptional<std::string>("groupsConfigurationFileCommand", p.groupsConfigurationFileCommand, j);
9422  getOptional<int>("groupsConfigurationFileCheckSecs", p.groupsConfigurationFileCheckSecs, j, 60);
9423  getOptional<EarServerStatusReportConfiguration>("statusReport", p.statusReport, j);
9424  getOptional<ExternalHealthCheckResponder>("externalHealthCheckResponder", p.externalHealthCheckResponder, j);
9425  getOptional<EarServerInternals>("internals", p.internals, j);
9426  getOptional<std::string>("certStoreFileName", p.certStoreFileName, j);
9427  getOptional<std::string>("certStorePasswordHex", p.certStorePasswordHex, j);
9428  j.at("enginePolicy").get_to(p.enginePolicy);
9429  getOptional<std::string>("configurationCheckSignalName", p.configurationCheckSignalName, j, "rts.6cc0651.${id}");
9430  }
